  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: feature request\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Status core team is on its way to migrate to Status Desktop as primary communication tool. In order to simplify desktop usage there is a suggestion to have channels (public chats) pinned at the left sidebar so user is not forced to join them manually each time nightly build is installed.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nwe can add list of public chats to the list of available public chats in the `Add new` screen. Once you add them, they will persist until account db is erased (to the left panel).\r\nIf user is updating desktop (not reinstalling) - those chats will be there forever which is quite handy.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/46417900-41713d80-c733-11e8-9cee-2da6ad63b870.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nThis option could be enabled in nightly builds only and disabled for public releases.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nI should join all the public chats each time manually. \r\n\r\n### List of chats to be added:\r\n\r\n- core\r\n- core-dapps\r\n- core-wallet\r\n- core-chat\r\n- core-wallet\r\n- core-releases\r\n- core-infra\r\n- designs\r\n- status-hardwallet-lite\r\n- test-team\r\n\r\nUPD use this https://hackmd.io/-9Gez_q-TGSAGW82VJVv1Q?e\r\n\r\nAnything else that i missed. Could be discussed (added later once requested)",
